**Important note on tail handling**: Only the pixel buffers (v16, v18) need zero-clearing because the same pixel data is reused across all 4 weight channels. The weight buffers are loaded freshly per channel and only used once, so their tail values do not matter (vd4dots with the zeroed pixel elements produces zero contribution regardless of weight tail values). This is the same logic as v2 which only clears v24/v28 (the pixel buffers) and not v16/v20 (the weight buffers).

### 4. Complete Epilogue Structure

After the inner loop completes, we have 8 M2 accumulators that need horizontal reduction, packing, and requantization.

#### 4.1 Horizontal Reduction (8 vredsum)

```c
        // Zero for vredsum identity
        NDS_VEC_VSETVLI(vl, 1, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_SEW_E32, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_LMUL_M1);
        NDS_VEC_VAND_VI(NDS_VEC_V31, NDS_VEC_V31, 0);

        // Set avl to cover all active accumulator elements
        NDS_VEC_VSETVLI(vl, num_col_a, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_SEW_E32, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_LMUL_M2);

        // Reduce all 8 accumulators → scalar in element 0 of destination
        // Reuse low registers for results since accumulators are consumed
        NDS_VEC_VREDSUM_VS(NDS_VEC_V28, NDS_VEC_V0,  NDS_VEC_V31);  // ch0*pix0 → v28[0]
        NDS_VEC_VREDSUM_VS(NDS_VEC_V29, NDS_VEC_V2,  NDS_VEC_V31);  // ch0*pix1 → v29[0]
        NDS_VEC_VREDSUM_VS(NDS_VEC_V30, NDS_VEC_V4,  NDS_VEC_V31);  // ch1*pix0 → v30[0]
```

Wait -- I need to be careful here. After the 8 vredsum operations, I need to pack 4 scalars for pix0 (ch0,ch1,ch2,ch3) into one vector register, and 4 scalars for pix1 into another. With only v28-v31 as scratch, I need to plan the sequencing carefully.

Let me reconsider the register allocation for the epilogue. After the inner loop, the accumulator registers (v0-v15) and load buffer registers (v16-v27) are all free to reuse. The issue is that VREDSUM writes the result into element [0] of the destination, and vslideup is needed to pack them.

Better approach -- do the reduction in pairs, packing as we go:

```c
        NDS_VEC_VSETVLI(vl, 1, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_SEW_E32, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_LMUL_M1);
        NDS_VEC_VAND_VI(NDS_VEC_V31, NDS_VEC_V31, 0);

        NDS_VEC_VSETVLI(vl, num_col_a, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_SEW_E32, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_LMUL_M2);
        // Pix0 results: need ch0,ch1,ch2,ch3 packed into one vector
        NDS_VEC_VREDSUM_VS(NDS_VEC_V16, NDS_VEC_V0,  NDS_VEC_V31);  // ch0*pix0 → v16[0]
        NDS_VEC_VREDSUM_VS(NDS_VEC_V17, NDS_VEC_V4,  NDS_VEC_V31);  // ch1*pix0 → v17[0]
        NDS_VEC_VREDSUM_VS(NDS_VEC_V18, NDS_VEC_V8,  NDS_VEC_V31);  // ch2*pix0 → v18[0]
        NDS_VEC_VREDSUM_VS(NDS_VEC_V19, NDS_VEC_V12, NDS_VEC_V31);  // ch3*pix0 → v19[0]

        // Pix1 results
        NDS_VEC_VREDSUM_VS(NDS_VEC_V20, NDS_VEC_V2,  NDS_VEC_V31);  // ch0*pix1 → v20[0]
        NDS_VEC_VREDSUM_VS(NDS_VEC_V21, NDS_VEC_V6,  NDS_VEC_V31);  // ch1*pix1 → v21[0]
        NDS_VEC_VREDSUM_VS(NDS_VEC_V22, NDS_VEC_V10, NDS_VEC_V31);  // ch2*pix1 → v22[0]
        NDS_VEC_VREDSUM_VS(NDS_VEC_V23, NDS_VEC_V14, NDS_VEC_V31);  // ch3*pix1 → v23[0]
```

#### 4.2 Pack via vslideup

Pack 4 scalars into a single VL=4 vector:

```c
        // Pack pix0: v16[0]=ch0, need ch1@[1], ch2@[2], ch3@[3]
        NDS_VEC_VSETVLI(vl, 2, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_SEW_E32, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_LMUL_M1);
        NDS_VEC_VSLIDEUP_VI(NDS_VEC_V16, NDS_VEC_V17, 1);   // v16 = [ch0, ch1]

        NDS_VEC_VSETVLI(vl, 3, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_SEW_E32, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_LMUL_M1);
        NDS_VEC_VSLIDEUP_VI(NDS_VEC_V16, NDS_VEC_V18, 2);   // v16 = [ch0, ch1, ch2]

        NDS_VEC_VSETVLI(vl, 4, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_SEW_E32, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_LMUL_M1);
        NDS_VEC_VSLIDEUP_VI(NDS_VEC_V16, NDS_VEC_V19, 3);   // v16 = [ch0, ch1, ch2, ch3]

        // Pack pix1: same pattern
        NDS_VEC_VSETVLI(vl, 2, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_SEW_E32, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_LMUL_M1);
        NDS_VEC_VSLIDEUP_VI(NDS_VEC_V20, NDS_VEC_V21, 1);

        NDS_VEC_VSETVLI(vl, 3, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_SEW_E32, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_LMUL_M1);
        NDS_VEC_VSLIDEUP_VI(NDS_VEC_V20, NDS_VEC_V22, 2);

        NDS_VEC_VSETVLI(vl, 4, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_SEW_E32, NDS_VEC_VTYPE_LMUL_M1);
        NDS_VEC_VSLIDEUP_VI(NDS_VEC_V20, NDS_VEC_V23, 3);
```

Note: This is 6 vslideup operations (3 per pixel) versus 2 in v2. The v2 epilogue only needs 1 vslideup per pixel because it packs 2 elements. This is the cost of the wider tile -- 4 extra vslideup instructions per tile, but we run 4x fewer tiles.

